UAS INCIDENT: 2212 The Pilot of AAL1678departing RWY 27R reported a white UAS over RWY 27R moving S bound across the airport. ATL ATCT also observed the UAS flying across the Airport S bound towards the approach area for RWY 27L just as DAL2046 was on short-final to this Runway. ATL ATCT instructed DAL2046 tocancel itsapproach and go-around due to the close proximity of the UAS. ATL ATCT also observed a grey and black SUV parked on the access road on the S side of the Airport and an individual standing outside the vehicle who appeared to be controlling the UAS. The Individual quicklygot in his vehicle and left the areaafter the DAL2046 approach was disrupted. ATL Airport Operations was notified and they dispatched a vehicle to patrol the area with negative results. TSOC notified. MR notified.

At 0155 ATCT observed a UAS fly over the field, W bound at 400-500 feet, 1 NM W of GSO Airport. Arrivals will be utilizing RWY 23L. Local Police and Fire Department are continuing to sweep airport and perimeter for operator. 0238 UPDATE: GSO ATCT reports last sighting approximately 0230, UAS was N of the airport flying E/W lines. Operations returning to normal configuration, arriving and departing RWY 23L. GSO ATCT will file MOR. 0250 UPDATE: GSO ATCT observed the large UAS transition over the airport W to E, turning S at approximately 600 feet. UAS impacting airfield operations. Air Traffic Manager has directed ATCT to suspend operations UFN. Airfield Operations, Local Police and Fire Department continue to sweep airfield and perimeter for operator. 4 IFR arrivals potentially impacted for the 0400 hour, ZTL will track and report diversions and/or delays. 0335 UPDATE: NOTAM GSO 02/174 issued for UAS activity. AWO reports COVID-19 Vaccine Flight, FDX1041, is delaying departure at ORD due to UAS ongoing event. 0430 UPDATE: 0406 GSO ATCT reports UAS sighting by Airport Operations 1/2 NM N of Airport, N bound heading towards HWY 73. 0415 GSO ATCT reports UAS sighting by Airport Operations NE of the Airport on the extended centerline RWY 23L. Approximately 0400 ATCSCC has issued a Ground Stop for Air Traffic into GSO. ATCSCC reports 1 aircraft diversion, 7 aircraft in airborne holding, 7 aircraft captured in the Ground Stop as of 0430. FDX Operations still holding COVID-19 Vaccine flight on the ground in ORD to minimize risk of airborne holding or diversion. 0435 UPDATE: AMOC has been monitoring GSO UAS event and has observed no radar returns. GSO ATCT reports they have had no radar returns from UAS activity, however visual sightings reported by the ATCT, LEO and Airfield Operations. 0435 UPDATE: GSO Airfield Operations reports last verified/confirmed sighting was approximately 0300, UAS had steady green, flashing red lights and made no noise. Subsequent reports of UAS are unconfirmed by Airport Operations. 3 LEO Agencies are now involved in securing the airport perimeter and monitoring operations. 0440 CLOSEOUT: GSO ATCT reports to the ATCSCC they are now going to start accepting arrivals and departures, last sighting N of the airport. ATCSCC has notified FDX and stakeholders. AWO, JH, CT notified.
